tourBios.carHigh: 2015: Made two starts on the Web.com Tour...His first career cut came at the News Sentinel Open in his second start, a T42 finish.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was voted Big West Freshman of the Year while attending Long Beach State in 2011-12...Two-time Southern California Amateur runner-up (2012-13)... 2014 California State Amateur Champion... Earned All-American honors in 2014-15 at San Diego State University...Holds the all-time season birdie and eagle record at San Diego State.
tourBios.personal: When he was 16, shot 6-under in three holes at Barona Creek GC in 2010...Not many people know he is the only natural-born U.S. citizen in his family...His father, Stefan, taught him the game and has been his only coach through his career, except for putting (Derek Uyeda).

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour in 2016 is T12th at the Servientrega Championship Presented by Efecty.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks 37th in Scoring Average (Actual) on the Web.com Tour.
